# UI Rules

## Core Principles

- Always use **shadcn/ui components** when available.
- Never rebuild components that already exist in shadcn/ui.
- Prefer **composition over custom UI implementation**.
- UI must be consistent across the entire app.

---

## Design System

- Use **Tailwind CSS only** for styling.
- Avoid inline styles.
- Do not introduce custom CSS files unless necessary.
- Use design tokens from shadcn/ui.

---

## Component Usage

Preferred components:

- Button
- Input
- Card
- Dialog
- Dropdown Menu
- Tabs
- Table
- Badge
- Avatar
- Skeleton
- Tooltip
- Sheet
- Select

Example:

```tsx
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";

export function Example() {
  return <Button>Click me</Button>;
}
```

---

## Class Management

- Use `cn()` utility for conditional classes.
- Avoid string concatenation for className.

Example:

```ts
className={cn("flex items-center", isActive && "text-blue-500")}
```

---

## Icons

- Use **Lucide React** for all icons.
- Do not use custom SVGs unless necessary.

Example:

```tsx
import { User } from "lucide-react";
```

---

## Layout Rules

- Use flex and grid instead of manual positioning.
- Prefer responsive design by default.
- Mobile-first approach.

---

## Form UI

- Use `react-hook-form` + `zod`.
- Always use shadcn/ui form components.
- Show validation errors clearly.

---

## Accessibility

- All interactive elements must be accessible.
- Ensure:
  - keyboard navigation works
  - aria labels exist when needed
  - focus states are visible

---

## Visual Consistency

- Maintain consistent:
  - spacing (Tailwind scale)
  - font sizes
  - border radius
  - button styles
- Avoid random custom styles per page.

---

## Component Structure

- Prefer reusable UI components in:

```
components/ui/
components/shared/
```

- Do not duplicate UI logic across features.

---

## Dark Mode

- Support dark mode by default (shadcn/ui standard).
- Do not hardcode colors.
- Use theme-aware classes.

---

## Anti-patterns (DO NOT DO)

- ❌ Rebuilding shadcn components manually
- ❌ Using random custom CSS per page
- ❌ Inline styles (`style={{}}`)
- ❌ Inconsistent button styles across pages
- ❌ SVG icons scattered across codebase
- ❌ Overusing div instead of proper UI components

---

## Goal

Build UI that is:

- Consistent
- Accessible
- Reusable
- Maintainable
- Aligned with shadcn/ui system